{"questionId":"33389618","questionHtml":"<p>Verify that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math> contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>substitute their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi></math> into equation of plane <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>λ</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></math></p>\n<p>so the line is contained in the plane<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: For FT from an incorrect part (a), award <em><strong>M1A0A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>consider the direction of the line <strong>and</strong> a point on the line<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; (so line is parallel to plane) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></math>&nbsp; (so line lies in the plane)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so the line is contained in the plane<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Both <strong><em>A</em></strong> marks are dependent on the <em><strong>M</strong></em> mark.</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: For FT from an incorrect part (a), award <em><strong>M1A0A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33389618","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.11c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Verify that Π contains L.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}